-- BUZZ-Shake-up at healthcare unit lifts Philips shares
-- 
-- Tue Jul 08, 2014 09:12AM EDT
-- None



July 8 (Reuters) -    ** Shares in Dutch healthcare and lighting company Philips <PHG.AS> are up more than 3.5 percent at the top of a 0.4 percent weaker Amsterdam blue chip index <.AEX>.

** Company tells its chief executive would take direct charge of the unit, which contributes 40 percent of company revenues. [ID:nL6N0PJ1G2] ** Philips says healthcare would perform better in the second half than last year. ** Philips shares have lost 10 percent so far this year. They are underperforming the AEX which has gained almost 3 percent since the start of the year.   (Reuters Messaging: thomas.escritt.thomsonreuters@reuters.net)